        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2594039586" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17667907732969187202">I don&apos;t like books that focus too much on the sexual activities of their characters and I felt this book did. I don&apos;t care about how many soldiers Minami wants to sleep with and the countless repetition bored me to death. <br/><br/>Also, the narrator&apos;s own experiences with the &apos;little girl&apos;. She is always referred to as &apos;the little girl&apos;. Jst how old was she? Was she even of age, was there even consent? I&apos;m horrified. I didn&apos;t like this book. <br/><br/>Okay my review is focusing on details that aren&apos;t even what the</span>
  <span id="freeText17667907732969187202" style="display:none">I don't like books that focus too much on the sexual activities of their characters and I felt this book did. I don't care about how many soldiers Minami wants to sleep with and the countless repetition bored me to death. <br /><br />Also, the narrator's own experiences with the 'little girl'. She is always referred to as 'the little girl'. Jst how old was she? Was she even of age, was there even consent? I'm horrified. I didn't like this book. <br /><br />Okay my review is focusing on details that aren't even what the story is about but these little details really put me off. So that's that.</span>
