    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3562038409" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3562038409" />
    <a title="Hayden Marks" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66937274-hayden-marks"><img alt="Hayden Marks" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1492306282p2/66937274.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3562038409?book_show_action=true">Sep 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hayden Marks" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hayden Marks" href="/user/show/66937274-hayden-marks">Hayden Marks</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3562038409" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5314925608845424939">A slow burn for such a short book. A very grim read that gets more and more brutal as it goes on. The comparisons to lord of the flies are valid but I would say this is definitely the better of the two. His writing style won’t be for everyone - it kinda reminds me of Hemingway, with a precedence for direct story telling rather than describing everything in detail to paint a more believable and compelling picture. Recommend for anyone looking for something grim. Which, in 2020 at least, probably </span>
  <span id="freeText5314925608845424939" style="display:none">A slow burn for such a short book. A very grim read that gets more and more brutal as it goes on. The comparisons to lord of the flies are valid but I would say this is definitely the better of the two. His writing style won’t be for everyone - it kinda reminds me of Hemingway, with a precedence for direct story telling rather than describing everything in detail to paint a more believable and compelling picture. Recommend for anyone looking for something grim. Which, in 2020 at least, probably isn’t all that necessary.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5314925608845424939" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
