<div id="review_1019347869" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1019347869" />
    <a title="Michael Mahin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15295925-michael-mahin"><img alt="Michael Mahin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1415573627p2/15295925.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1019347869?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Mahin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Mahin" href="/user/show/15295925-michael-mahin">Michael Mahin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15295925-michael-mahin?shelf=nobel-prize-winners">nobel-prize-winners</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15295925-michael-mahin?shelf=existentialism">existentialism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15295925-michael-mahin?shelf=world-literature">world-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15295925-michael-mahin?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15295925-michael-mahin?shelf=literary-fiction">literary-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1019347869" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16791053312061614383">Long before winning the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1994, Oe was studying French Literature at Tokyo University, where he did his graduate thesis on Jean-Paul Sartre. It&apos;s no surprise then that many of Oe&apos;s works deal with various forms of existential crisis. Nip the Buds, which is an exploration of innocence confronting the tragic realities of experience, fits this profile. <br/><br/>Nip the Buds if often described as a Japanese Lord of the Flies. In it, 15 unloved and unwanted reformatory boys are &quot;qua</span>
  <span id="freeText16791053312061614383" style="display:none">Long before winning the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1994, Oe was studying French Literature at Tokyo University, where he did his graduate thesis on Jean-Paul Sartre. It's no surprise then that many of Oe's works deal with various forms of existential crisis. Nip the Buds, which is an exploration of innocence confronting the tragic realities of experience, fits this profile. <br /><br />Nip the Buds if often described as a Japanese Lord of the Flies. In it, 15 unloved and unwanted reformatory boys are "quarantined" by local villagers when a plague breaks out. Left to fend for themselves, the boys search for meaning in the face of death and beneath the shadow of war. Like the Lord of the Flies, Nip the Bud's themes reflect modern anxieties over the tragic complexities of war as experienced by the young.<br /><br />Written in 1958, Nip the Buds also reflects Japanese cultural anxieties about finding meaning in a post-WWII, post-Hiroshima/Nagasaki, post-emperor world. The story itself is written in a straighforward, first person narration. As with Lord of the Flies, major themes include war, death, justice vs moral good, the loss of innocence, friendship, love, cowardice, class, and survival.<br /><br />If you're a lover of world literature, existentialism, philosophical books like Dostoevsky's Notes from the Underground, or dark coming of age stories like Lord of the Flies, Catcher in the Rye, and A Separate Peace, you'll love Nip the Buds. I did.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16791053312061614383" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

